    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="44"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d44fn1">Sent to Washington by the United States Military
                        Attaché, London, via Army channels; forwarded by the White House Map Room to
                        Roosevelt, who was spending the Labor Day weekend at Hyde Park, as telegram
                        No. <gloss target="#t_Red1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Red</hi>
                        </gloss> 346.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-01">1st September
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President Roosevelt. No. 775 Personal and Top Secret.</p>
                <p>My temperature is normal and I am much better though still eating masses of M and
                    B. The doctors seem quite confident that I can get away on night of fifth.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d44fn2">For Winant’s comments on Churchill’s health, sent to
                        Hopkins on September 1, 1944, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_254">p. 254</ref>.</note> The ship goes to <gloss
                        target="#t_Halifax1">Halifax</gloss> direct and I will arrive Citadel on the
                    tenth.</p>
                <pb facs="0082" n="28" xml:id="pg_28"/>
                <p>I look forward so much to seeing you again and to making good plans with you for
                    the future in these days of glory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <gloss target="#t_Prime1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prime</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
